    </draw:frame><draw:frame draw:style-name="fr4" draw:name="Frame1" text:anchor-type="char" svg:x="2.5189in" svg:y="1.4874in" svg:width="1.902in" svg:height="0.6in" draw:z-index="14">
     <draw:text-box>
      <text:p text:style-name="Standard"><text:span text:style-name="T1">energia finale </text:span><text:span text:style-name="T2">E</text:span><text:span text:style-name="T3">f</text:span></text:p>
     </draw:text-box>
    </draw:frame><draw:frame draw:style-name="fr4" draw:name="Frame2" text:anchor-type="char" svg:x="2.5189in" svg:y="0.6874in" svg:width="1.902in" svg:height="0.6in" draw:z-index="13">
     <draw:text-box>
      <text:p text:style-name="Standard"><text:span text:style-name="T1">energia iniziale </text:span><text:span text:style-name="T2">E</text:span><text:span text:style-name="T3">i</text:span></text:p>
     </draw:text-box>
    </draw:frame>Nella sesta scheda abbiamo visto che l’energia dell’atomo di idrogeno è quantizzata; ora ci chiediamo cosa succede quando un atomo passa da uno stato energetico superiore ad uno inferiore?</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Standard"/>
   <text:p text:style-name="Standard">Per capire questo fenomeno è necessario studiare la Meccanica Quantistica Relativistica, comunque per ora ci basta sapere due cose:</text:p>
   <text:list text:style-name="WW8Num1">
    <text:list-item>
     <text:p text:style-name="P4">primo, che quando un atomo riceve una certa energia da un sistema esterno e si porta in uno stato “eccitato”, cioè uno stato ad energia superiore, non rimane a lungo in questa condizione ma “decade” in uno stato di energia più bassa in un tempo brevissimo;</text:p>
    </text:list-item>
    <text:list-item>
     <text:p text:style-name="P4">secondo, quando l’atomo decade in uno stato di energia inferiore, emette un fotone con energia pari alla differenza <draw:frame draw:style-name="fr5" draw:name="Object5" text:anchor-type="as-char" svg:width="0.4846in" svg:height="0.222in" draw:z-index="0"><draw:object>
        <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="block">
         <semantics>
          <mrow>
           <mstyle mathsize="12pt">
            <mrow>
             <msub>
              <mi>E</mi>
              <mstyle mathsize="8pt">
               <mi>i</mi>
              </mstyle>
             </msub>
             <mo stretchy="false">−</mo>
             <msub>
              <mi>E</mi>
              <mstyle mathsize="8pt">
               <mi>f</mi>
              </mstyle>
             </msub>
            </mrow>
           </mstyle>
           <mrow/>
          </mrow>
          <annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0"> size 12{E rSub { size 8{i} }  - E rSub { size 8{f} } } {}</annotation>
         </semantics>
        </math>
       </draw:object><draw:image>
        <office:binary-data>AQAJAAAD4gAAAAIAFQAAAAAABQAAAAkCAAAAAAQAAAACAQEABQAAAAEC////AAQAAAAuARgA
         BQAAADECAQAAAAUAAAALAgAAAAAFAAAADAKgAsAGEgAAACYGDwAaAP////8AABAAAADA////
         t////4AGAABXAgAACwAAACYGDwAMAE1hdGhUeXBlAACAABUAAAD7AiD/AAAAAAAAkAEBAAAA
         BAIAEFRpbWVzIE5ldyBSb21hbgAAfwQAAAAtAQAACAAAADIKEAIJBgEAAABmAAgAAAAyChAC
         jwEBAAAAaQAVAAAA+wJA/gAAAAAAAJABAQAAAAQCABBUaW1lcyBOZXcgUm9tYW4AAH8EAAAA
         LQEBAAQAAADwAQAACAAAADIKoAGRBAEAAABFAAgAAAAyCqABRwABAAAARQAQAAAA+wJA/gAA
         AAAAAJABAAAAAgQCABBTeW1ib2wAAgQAAAAtAQAABAAAAPABAQAIAAAAMgqgAeMCAQAAAC0A
         CgAAACYGDwAKAP////8BAAAAAAAQAAAA+wIUAAkAAAAAALwCAAAAAAECAiJTeXN0ZW0AAAQA
         AAAtAQEABAAAAPABAAADAAAAAAA=
        </office:binary-data>
       </draw:image>
      </draw:frame>.</text:p>
    </text:list-item>
   </text:list>
   <text:p text:style-name="Standard">In base alla relazione di Einstein <draw:frame draw:style-name="fr5" draw:name="Object6" text:anchor-type="as-char" svg:width="0.4465in" svg:height="0.1854in" draw:z-index="1"><draw:object>
      <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="block">
       <semantics>
        <mrow>
         <mstyle mathsize="12pt">
          <mrow>
           <mi>E</mi>
           <mo stretchy="false">=</mo>
           <mi mathvariant="italic">hν</mi>
          </mrow>
         </mstyle>
         <mrow/>
        </mrow>
        <annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0"> size 12{E=hν} {}</annotation>
       </semantics>
      </math>
     </draw:object><draw:image>
      <office:binary-data>AQAJAAAD1QAAAAIAFQAAAAAABQAAAAkCAAAAAAQAAAACAQEABQAAAAEC////AAQAAAAuARgA
       BQAAADECAQAAAAUAAAALAgAAAAAFAAAADALgAQAGEgAAACYGDwAaAP////8AABAAAADA////
       1////8AFAAC3AQAACwAAACYGDwAMAE1hdGhUeXBlAAAwABAAAAD7AkD+AAAAAAAAkAEBAAAC
       BAIAEFN5bWJvbAACBAAAAC0BAAAIAAAAMgqAAZgEAQAAAG4AFQAAAPsCQP4AAAAAAACQAQEA
       AAAEAgAQVGltZXMgTmV3IFJvbWFuAAB/BAAAAC0BAQAEAAAA8AEAAAgAAAAyCoABuAMBAAAA
       aAAIAAAAMgqAAUcAAQAAAEUAEAAAAPsCQP4AAAAAAACQAQAAAAIEAgAQU3ltYm9sAAIEAAAA
       LQEAAAQAAADwAQEACAAAADIKgAEYAgEAAAA9AAoAAAAmBg8ACgD/////AQAAAAAAEAAAAPsC
       FAAJAAAAAAC8AgAAAAABAgIiU3lzdGVtAAAEAAAALQEBAAQAAADwAQAAAwAAAAAA
      </office:binary-data>
     </draw:image>
    </draw:frame><text:s/>noi possiamo determinare l’energia di un fotone misurando la frequenza dell’onda elettromagnetica associata. Dunque, mettendo insieme questi fatti, abbiamo un metodo per determinare le differenze di energia tra i vari stati di un atomo.</text:p>
   <text:h text:style-name="Heading_20_2" text:outline-level="2">Descrizione di principio dell’esperimento.</text:h>
   <text:list text:style-name="WW8Num3">
    <text:list-item>
     <text:p text:style-name="P5">Si prende la sostanza che si vuole analizzare e la si porta allo stato gassoso, in questo modo abbiamo un insieme di atomi indipendenti tra di loro.</text:p>
    </text:list-item>
    <text:list-item>
     <text:p text:style-name="P5">Si fornisce energia a questi atomi in modo da “eccitarli”, cioè in modo da portarli ad uno stato energetico superiore.</text:p>
    </text:list-item>
    <text:list-item>
     <text:p text:style-name="P5">Si raccoglie la luce emessa dagli atomi e si misurano le varie frequenze di cui è composta.</text:p>
    </text:list-item>
    <text:list-item>
     <text:p text:style-name="P5">In base alla relazione di Einstein <draw:frame draw:style-name="fr5" draw:name="Object7" text:anchor-type="as-char" svg:width="0.4465in" svg:height="0.1854in" draw:z-index="2"><draw:object>
        <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="block">
         <semantics>
          <mrow>
           <mstyle mathsize="12pt">
            <mrow>
             <mi>E</mi>
             <mo stretchy="false">=</mo>
             <mi mathvariant="italic">hν</mi>
            </mrow>
           </mstyle>
           <mrow/>
          </mrow>
          <annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0"> size 12{E=hν} {}</annotation>
         </semantics>
        </math>
       </draw:object><draw:image>
        <office:binary-data>AQAJAAAD1QAAAAIAFQAAAAAABQAAAAkCAAAAAAQAAAACAQEABQAAAAEC////AAQAAAAuARgA
         BQAAADECAQAAAAUAAAALAgAAAAAFAAAADALgAQAGEgAAACYGDwAaAP////8AABAAAADA////
         1////8AFAAC3AQAACwAAACYGDwAMAE1hdGhUeXBlAAAwABAAAAD7AkD+AAAAAAAAkAEBAAAC
         BAIAEFN5bWJvbAACBAAAAC0BAAAIAAAAMgqAAZgEAQAAAG4AFQAAAPsCQP4AAAAAAACQAQEA
         AAAEAgAQVGltZXMgTmV3IFJvbWFuAAB/BAAAAC0BAQAEAAAA8AEAAAgAAAAyCoABuAMBAAAA
         aAAIAAAAMgqAAUcAAQAAAEUAEAAAAPsCQP4AAAAAAACQAQAAAAIEAgAQU3ltYm9sAAIEAAAA
         LQEAAAQAAADwAQEACAAAADIKgAEYAgEAAAA9AAoAAAAmBg8ACgD/////AQAAAAAAEAAAAPsC
         FAAJAAAAAAC8AgAAAAABAgIiU3lzdGVtAAAEAAAALQEBAAQAAADwAQAAAwAAAAAA
        </office:binary-data>
       </draw:image>
      </draw:frame><text:s/>si derivano i vari dislivelli energetici dell’atomo sotto studio.</text:p>
    </text:list-item>
   </text:list>
   <text:p text:style-name="Standard">Per misurare le frequenze si può usare un reticolo di diffrazione che produce il primo massimo ad un angolo che dipende dalla frequenza della luce incidente:</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Standard"><text:tab/><draw:frame draw:style-name="fr5" draw:name="Object8" text:anchor-type="as-char" svg:width="2.4291in" svg:height="0.3953in" draw:z-index="3"><draw:object>
      <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="block">
       <semantics>
        <mrow>
         <mstyle mathsize="12pt">
          <mrow>
           <mrow>
            <mfrac>
             <mi>λ</mi>
             <mi>d</mi>
            </mfrac>
            <mo stretchy="false">=</mo>
            <mtext>sen</mtext>
           </mrow>
           <mi>ϑ</mi>
           <mo stretchy="false">⇔</mo>
           <mrow>
            <mfrac>
             <mi>c</mi>
             <mi mathvariant="italic">νd</mi>
            </mfrac>
            <mo stretchy="false">=</mo>
            <mtext>sen</mtext>
           </mrow>
           <mi>ϑ</mi>
           <mo stretchy="false">⇔</mo>
           <mrow>
            <mi>ν</mi>
            <mo stretchy="false">=</mo>
            <mfrac>
             <mi>c</mi>
             <mrow>
              <mi>d</mi>
              <mtext>sen</mtext>
              <mi>ϑ</mi>
             </mrow>
            </mfrac>
           </mrow>
          </mrow>
         </mstyle>
         <mrow/>
        </mrow>
        <annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0"> size 12{ {  {λ}  over  {d} } =&quot;sen&quot;ϑ dlrarrow  {  {c}  over  {νd} } =&quot;sen&quot;ϑ dlrarrow ν= {  {c}  over  {d&quot;sen&quot;ϑ} } } {}</annotation>
       </semantics>
      </math>
     </draw:object><draw:image>
      <office:binary-data>AQAJAAADmAEAAAMAFQAAAAAABQAAAAkCAAAAAAQAAAACAQEABQAAAAEC////AAQAAAAuARgA
       BQAAADECAQAAAAUAAAALAgAAAAAFAAAADAKABEAbEgAAACYGDwAaAP////8AABAAAADA////
       r////wAbAAAvBAAACwAAACYGDwAMAE1hdGhUeXBlAADgAAkAAAD6AgAAEAAAAAAAAAAiAAQA
       AAAtAQAABQAAABQCUAJAAAUAAAATAlACdQEFAAAAFAJQAncJBQAAABMCUAJUCwUAAAAUAlAC
       +BUFAAAAEwJQAvAaEAAAAPsCQP4AAAAAAACQAQEAAAIEAgAQU3ltYm9sAAIEAAAALQEBAAgA
       AAAyChwEqhkBAAAASgAIAAAAMgrAAhATAQAAAG4ACAAAADIKwAJ5DwEAAABKAAgAAAAyChwE
       UQkBAAAAbgAIAAAAMgrAApoFAQAAAEoACAAAADIKqAFSAAEAAABsABUAAAD7AkD+AAAAAAAA
       kAEAAAAABAIAEFRpbWVzIE5ldyBSb21hbgAAfgQAAAAtAQIABAAAAPABAQAJAAAAMgocBEAX
       AwAAAHNlbgAJAAAAMgrAAg8NAwAAAHNlbgAJAAAAMgrAAjADAwAAAHNlbgAVAAAA+wJA/gAA
       AAAAAJABAQAAAAQCABBUaW1lcyBOZXcgUm9tYW4AAH4EAAAALQEBAAQAAADwAQIACAAAADIK
       HAQRFgEAAABkAAgAAAAyCqgBDxgBAAAAYwAIAAAAMgocBDgKAQAAAGQACAAAADIKqAEACgEA
       AABjAAgAAAAyChwEWQABAAAAZAAQAAAA+wJA/gAAAAAAAJABAAAAAgQCABBTeW1ib2wAAgQA
       AAAtAQIABAAAAPABAQAIAAAAMgrAApkUAQAAAD0ACAAAADIKwAIQEQEAAADbAAgAAAAyCsAC
       xQsBAAAAPQAIAAAAMgrAAjEHAQAAANsACAAAADIKwALmAQEAAAA9AAoAAAAmBg8ACgD/////
       AQAAAAAAEAAAAPsCFAAJAAAAAAC8AgAAAAABAgIiU3lzdGVtAAAEAAAALQEBAAQAAADwAQIA
       AwAAAAAA
      </office:binary-data>
     </draw:image>
    </draw:frame></text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Standard">Se inviamo un fascio di luce prodotta dagli atomi verso un reticolo di diffrazione, al di là del reticolo abbiamo una separazione del fascio in varie parti monocromatiche, ogni singola parte sarà deflessa con un angolo diverso; misurando gli angoli di diffrazione si determinano le frequenze di cui è composto il fascio.</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Standard"><draw:frame draw:style-name="fr4" draw:name="Frame3" text:anchor-type="char" svg:x="2.8071in" svg:y="1.6075in" svg:width="0.8in" svg:height="0.5in" draw:z-index="28">
     <draw:text-box>
      <text:p text:style-name="P6">E (eV)</text:p>
     </draw:text-box>
    </draw:frame>L’atomo più semplice che ha anche lo spettro più semplice è l’atomo di idrogeno. I livelli energetici previsti dalla teoria per l’atomo di idrogeno sono <text:soft-page-break/>dati dalla formula <draw:frame draw:style-name="fr5" draw:name="Object9" text:anchor-type="as-char" svg:width="1.0665in" svg:height="0.4835in" draw:z-index="4"><draw:object>
      <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="block">
       <semantics>
        <mrow>
         <mstyle mathsize="12pt">
          <mrow>
           <msub>
            <mi>E</mi>
            <mstyle mathsize="8pt">
             <mi>n</mi>
            </mstyle>
           </msub>
           <mo stretchy="false">=</mo>
           <mrow>
            <mo stretchy="false">−</mo>
            <mfrac>
             <mstyle mathvariant="italic">
              <msup>
               <mtext>me</mtext>
               <mstyle mathsize="8pt">
                <mn>4</mn>
               </mstyle>
              </msup>
             </mstyle>
             <mrow>
              <mn>8</mn>
              <msub>
               <mi>ε</mi>
               <mstyle mathsize="8pt">
                <mn>0</mn>
               </mstyle>
              </msub>
              <msup>
               <mi>h</mi>
               <mstyle mathsize="8pt">
                <mn>2</mn>
               </mstyle>
              </msup>
              <msup>
               <mi>n</mi>
               <mstyle mathsize="8pt">
                <mn>2</mn>
               </mstyle>
              </msup>
             </mrow>
            </mfrac>
           </mrow>
          </mrow>
         </mstyle>
         <mrow/>
        </mrow>
        <annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0"> size 12{E rSub { size 8{n} } = -  {  { ital &quot;me&quot; rSup { size 8{4} } }  over  {8ε rSub { size 8{0} } h rSup { size 8{2} } n rSup { size 8{2} } } } } {}</annotation>
       </semantics>
      </math>
     </draw:object><draw:image>
